1
00:00:02.419 --> 00:00:05.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. A little lower.

2
00:00:06.214 --> 00:00:07.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lower.

3
00:00:08.341 --> 00:00:09.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lower.

4
00:00:09.259 --> 00:00:10.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs softly )

5
00:00:11.803 --> 00:00:13.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's that?

6
00:00:13.221 --> 00:00:14.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

7
00:00:16.307 --> 00:00:18.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ODO: Well, I hope this taught
you a lesson.

8
00:00:19.352 --> 00:00:20.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

9
00:00:20.687 --> 00:00:24.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Never play spring ball
against a changeling.

10
00:00:24.858 --> 00:00:27.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, just for that, next time,

11
00:00:27.819 --> 00:00:30.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not going
to let you win a single game.

12
00:00:30.739 --> 00:00:33.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then you'd better work
on your backhand.

13
00:00:33.950 --> 00:00:34.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-mm.

14
00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:39.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Right now, all I want to do is just sleep
for two or three--

15
00:00:39.289 --> 00:00:41.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping ) oh, oh, oh...

16
00:00:41.374 --> 00:00:42.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Days.

17
00:00:42.917 --> 00:00:44.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go right ahead.

18
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:47.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should be back by the time you wake up.

19
00:00:47.797 --> 00:00:49.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Back? From where?

20
00:00:49.966 --> 00:00:54.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I received a coded message
from Gul Russol this morning.

21
00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:56.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gul Russol.

22
00:00:57.640 --> 00:01:01.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought he was executed
when Cardassia joined the Dominion.

23
00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:06.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So did I, but apparently we were wrong.
The message says he wants to meet with me.

24
00:01:06.441 --> 00:01:08.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why?
-I don't know,

25
00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:11.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but he's my most reliable
Cardassian informant.

26
00:01:11.905 --> 00:01:16.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean he was. What if Russol is dead
and this is just a trap?

27
00:01:16.326 --> 00:01:18.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've thought about that,
but I have to be sure.

28
00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:20.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I owe him that much.

29
00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:26.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Want me to come with you?
-Russol insists I come alone.

30
00:01:29.214 --> 00:01:32.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Nerys.
I'll be careful.

31
00:01:33.176 --> 00:01:35.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worried? Ha.

32
00:01:35.512 --> 00:01:38.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This just gives me more time to work
on my backhand.

33
00:01:38.348 --> 00:01:39.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

34
00:01:46.439 --> 00:01:47.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Chief!

35
00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:51.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How much longer is the Promenade
going to be closed?

36
00:01:51.945 --> 00:01:54.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My bar is empty. My waiters are bored.

37
00:01:54.781 --> 00:01:57.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-And I'm losing money.
-Leave me alone, Quark,

38
00:01:57.784 --> 00:02:00.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or I'll feed you to one
of those plasma conductors.

39
00:02:00.328 --> 00:02:03.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you threatening me?
-We're working as fast as we can.

40
00:02:04.457 --> 00:02:08.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As spokesman for the Promenade
Merchants' Association, I'm going to file

41
00:02:08.586 --> 00:02:12.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-an official protest with Captain Sisko.
-Put it in writing, Quark.

42
00:02:13.383 --> 00:02:14.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll go find a padd.

43
00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:19.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how much longer, Chief?

44
00:02:19.848 --> 00:02:22.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, we should be through here
by the end of the day, sir.

45
00:02:22.475 --> 00:02:25.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I'm not talking about the Promenade.
I'm talking about the <i>Defiant.</i>

46
00:02:25.728 --> 00:02:27.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When is the gravity net
going to be repaired?

47
00:02:27.981 --> 00:02:31.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The last time I stepped onto the Bridge,
I felt ten kilos heavier.

48
00:02:31.484 --> 00:02:35.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'm afraid it's going to take some time.
-How much time? About three weeks.

49
00:02:35.655 --> 00:02:38.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to replace
the graviton stabilizer.

50
00:02:38.241 --> 00:02:41.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have three days. I'm going to take
the <i>Defiant </i>back out on patrol,

51
00:02:41.619 --> 00:02:46.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I don't want my crew getting queasy
because the gravity keeps fluctuating.

52
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:48.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But, sir, the Sector Quartermaster said,

53
00:02:48.293 --> 00:02:51.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it would take three weeks
to get us a new stabilizer.

54
00:02:51.504 --> 00:02:53.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that is your problem, Chief.

55
00:02:53.798 --> 00:02:55.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, I'm leaving for Bajor
for a conference,

56
00:02:55.758 --> 00:02:59.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I want that stabilizer replaced
by the time I get back.

57
00:03:00.013 --> 00:03:01.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do I make myself clear?

58
00:03:01.097 --> 00:03:02.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

59
00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:08.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't mean to sound negative,
but I don't see

60
00:03:08.271 --> 00:03:10.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how you're going to get the <i>Defiant</i>
ready in three days.

61
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:11.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Neither do I.

62
00:03:14.819 --> 00:03:17.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This Quartermaster you've been dealing
with, what's his name?

63
00:03:18.489 --> 00:03:21.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, Chief... Chief... Chief Willoughby.

64
00:03:22.118 --> 00:03:24.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean his first name. I don't know.

65
00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:26.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is he married?
-Married?

66
00:03:26.581 --> 00:03:29.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What does that have to do with getting
us a graviton stabilizer?

67
00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:31.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything. This Chief Willoughby

68
00:03:31.461 --> 00:03:34.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
must get hundreds of supply requisitions
every day.

69
00:03:34.505 --> 00:03:38.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He can't possibly fill them all.
So he puts everyone on a waiting list.

70
00:03:38.176 --> 00:03:41.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know how he feels.
I do the same thing.

71
00:03:42.138 --> 00:03:44.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, the secret is getting him to put you

72
00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:47.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
at the top of that list,
and the best way to do that

73
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:49.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is to form a relationship with him.

74
00:03:49.354 --> 00:03:52.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
NOG: Get to know the name of his wife,
his children.

75
00:03:52.857 --> 00:03:54.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Find out what he likes to eat.

76
00:03:54.817 --> 00:03:57.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't have time to form
a relationship with Willoughby.

77
00:04:00.114 --> 00:04:00.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do.

78
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:04.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can get you that stabilizer, Chief.

79
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:07.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In three days? Leave everything to me.

80
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right. But don't do anything
I wouldn't do.

81
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:14.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, I can't operate
under those kinds of restrictions.

82
00:04:14.879 --> 00:04:18.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least promise me you won't do anything
to get us court-martialed.

83
00:04:20.802 --> 00:04:22.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll try.
-Nog!

84
00:04:22.887 --> 00:04:24.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just kidding, Chief.

85
00:04:24.305 --> 00:04:25.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

86
00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

87
00:04:48.162 --> 00:04:49.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Russol?

88
00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:56.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Russol?
-WEYOUN: I'm afraid he couldn't be here.

89
00:05:00.466 --> 00:05:01.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Weyoun.

90
00:05:06.014 --> 00:05:07.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Founder.

91
00:05:08.016 --> 00:05:11.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is an honor to stand
in your presence once again.

92
00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:13.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where's Gul Russol?

93
00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:18.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid the Cardassian Central Command
had him put to death almost a year ago.

94
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:21.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN: I regret having to deceive you,

95
00:05:21.654 --> 00:05:23.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it was the only way I could
think of to get you here.

96
00:05:24.240 --> 00:05:27.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm here.
What do you want?

97
00:05:28.077 --> 00:05:29.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To serve you.

98
00:05:31.372 --> 00:05:34.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I no longer consider myself
a member of the Dominion.

99
00:05:36.753 --> 00:05:38.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're defecting?

100
00:05:39.422 --> 00:05:40.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do with me as you wish.

101
00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:45.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I place my fate entirely in your hands.

102
00:07:47.633 --> 00:07:49.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't believe me, do you?

103
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:52.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I believe Gul Russol is dead.

104
00:07:53.598 --> 00:07:57.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You say you're defecting
from the Dominion? Why?

105
00:07:57.768 --> 00:08:01.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Founder, please...
-I've told you before, I'm not a Founder.

106
00:08:01.856 --> 00:08:02.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
As you wish.

107
00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:09.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Odo... I'll tell you
everything you want to know, but first,

108
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:11.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
we really should get aboard your runabout.

109
00:08:11.365 --> 00:08:14.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Jem'Hadar are already hunting for me,
and if I'm found--

110
00:08:14.368 --> 00:08:16.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You still haven't answered my question.

111
00:08:20.416 --> 00:08:23.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Why did you decide to defect?

112
00:08:23.711 --> 00:08:25.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I realized my place is with you.

113
00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:28.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You can do better than that.

114
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:34.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Then let's just say, I left Cardassia
because my life was in danger.

115
00:08:35.806 --> 00:08:37.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-From whom?
-Everyone.

116
00:08:38.476 --> 00:08:40.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Aren't you being a little paranoid?

117
00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Of course, I'm paranoid, everyone's trying
to kill me.

118
00:08:42.772 --> 00:08:45.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Why?
-Because this war with the Federation

119
00:08:45.316 --> 00:08:47.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
was supposed to have been won months ago.

120
00:08:48.027 --> 00:08:50.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, things don't always
turn out as planned.

121
00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:54.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Quite true... and when things go wrong,
someone has to take the blame

122
00:08:54.283 --> 00:08:55.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and this time, it's me.

123
00:08:56.744 --> 00:09:00.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Now...
we really should be going.

124
00:09:04.585 --> 00:09:10.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Think about it, Odo.
The information I possess

125
00:09:10.591 --> 00:09:13.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
could help the Federation win this war.

126
00:09:14.053 --> 00:09:17.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And you're willing
to share that information?

127
00:09:17.682 --> 00:09:18.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
All you have to do is ask.

128
00:09:22.186 --> 00:09:24.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We've heard rumors
that the Dominion has established

129
00:09:24.939 --> 00:09:29.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
a new ketracel-white storage facility
somewhere in sector 507.

130
00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:32.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The facility's located
in the Pelosa system.

131
00:09:32.613 --> 00:09:34.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can provide you
with the exact coordinates.

132
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:41.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo to the <i>Rio Grande,</i> two to beam up.

133
00:09:41.914 --> 00:09:43.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

134
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:53.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sit here, where I can keep an eye on you.

135
00:09:54.135 --> 00:09:55.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If it makes you feel better...

136
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:59.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you should know
I would never harm a God.

137
00:09:59.390 --> 00:10:02.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not a God. I'm a security officer.

138
00:10:02.101 --> 00:10:04.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As far as I'm concerned,
you're just another prisoner.

139
00:10:05.896 --> 00:10:09.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have no idea how much
it hurts me to hear you say that.

140
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:11.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

141
00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:21.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I spoke to Edgar.
-Edgar who?

142
00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:23.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your new best friend,
Chief Edgar Willoughby.

143
00:10:23.664 --> 00:10:26.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He wanted me to thank you for that bottle
of Gamzian wine you sent him.

144
00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:31.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I didn't send him any wine.
-I took the liberty of sending it for you.

145
00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:35.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By the way, his wife's name is Cynthia.
They have a daughter, Melissa, age eight,

146
00:10:35.885 --> 00:10:39.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-and a son, Edgar Jr., age five.
-Did you get the stabilizer?

147
00:10:39.180 --> 00:10:40.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Not quite.
-What do you mean, "not quite"?

148
00:10:41.015 --> 00:10:42.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unfortunately, he's out of stabilizers

149
00:10:42.933 --> 00:10:44.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and won't be getting a new shipment
for another week.

150
00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:46.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, well, that's it, I'm doomed.

151
00:10:46.479 --> 00:10:50.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not necessarily. Eddie told me
the USS <i>Sentinel</i> has an extra stabilizer.

152
00:10:50.900 --> 00:10:52.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What makes you think
they're going to give it to us?

153
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:54.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't say they were going
to give it to us...

154
00:10:55.071 --> 00:10:56.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but they might be willing to trade for it.

155
00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:58.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trade? For what?

156
00:10:58.282 --> 00:11:00.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Depends on what they need
and what we have.

157
00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:07.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I suppose it doesn't hurt to try.
But remember, be discreet.

158
00:11:07.291 --> 00:11:09.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rule of Acquisition 168,

159
00:11:09.835 --> 00:11:11.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Whisper your way to success."

160
00:11:11.671 --> 00:11:13.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckling ) Words to live by.

161
00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:16.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, one more thing.
I need your authorization code.

162
00:11:16.675 --> 00:11:18.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What for?
-The shipping orders.

163
00:11:18.594 --> 00:11:20.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bring them to me and I'll authorize them.

164
00:11:21.138 --> 00:11:22.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just thought it would save time.

165
00:11:22.973 --> 00:11:25.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When did you say the Captain
was going to be back?

166
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:28.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

167
00:11:29.021 --> 00:11:32.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Stop looking so worried, Chief.
I've got it all under control.

168
00:11:33.901 --> 00:11:35.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I sure hope so.

169
00:11:44.745 --> 00:11:46.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish you'd stop doing that.

170
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:48.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Doing what?
-Staring at me.

171
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:50.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was I? I didn't mean to.

172
00:11:51.252 --> 00:11:52.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've been doing it
for the last ten hours.

173
00:11:53.003 --> 00:11:56.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry.
It's just such an honor to be sitting here

174
00:11:56.799 --> 00:11:57.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with a G--

175
00:11:58.926 --> 00:12:00.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Security officer.

176
00:12:01.762 --> 00:12:02.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

177
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:05.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're being hailed.
-WEYOUN: Don't respond.

178
00:12:06.851 --> 00:12:09.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's a Cardassian transmission.
-Scramble the com frequencies

179
00:12:09.937 --> 00:12:12.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-So they can't lock onto us.
-I'm trying.

180
00:12:13.941 --> 00:12:19.029  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Founder... it's an honor to speak </i>
<i>with you again.</i>

181
00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:31.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-You look surprised to see me, Odo.</i>
-I'm well aware the Vorta are all clones,

182
00:12:32.001 --> 00:12:35.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I'm not sure the universe
is ready for two Weyouns.

183
00:12:35.588 --> 00:12:37.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I couldn't agree more.</i>

184
00:12:38.007 --> 00:12:41.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, which of you is the Weyoun

185
00:12:41.677 --> 00:12:44.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've had the misfortune of dealing
with over the past few years?

186
00:12:45.181 --> 00:12:46.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually, neither of us.

187
00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:52.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That was Weyoun 5. Our illustrious </i>
<i>predecessor</i> <i>was killed a month ago.</i>

188
00:12:53.397 --> 00:12:55.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I had the honor of replacing him.

189
00:12:55.858 --> 00:13:01.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>What a sad day that was for the Dominion.</i>
<i>Weyoun 5 was a great man, a true patriot.</i>

190
00:13:02.114 --> 00:13:06.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His death in a transporter...
accident was most unfortunate.

191
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:09.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN 6: <i>And still under investigation.</i>

192
00:13:10.247 --> 00:13:13.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A very thorough investigation
that has found no evidence of foul play.

193
00:13:14.084 --> 00:13:15.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Interesting.

194
00:13:15.961 --> 00:13:20.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, if you're Weyoun 6, you must be 7.

195
00:13:20.424 --> 00:13:24.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Clones, keeping track
of them is a full-time job.

196
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:27.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And why were you activated
if he's still alive?

197
00:13:27.723 --> 00:13:31.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Normally, I wouldn't have been, but when
a clone is found to be defective...

198
00:13:31.352 --> 00:13:33.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'm not defective.
-WEYOUN 7: <i>Of course you are.</i>

199
00:13:33.521 --> 00:13:35.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What other explanation is there
for your behavior?

200
00:13:36.023 --> 00:13:38.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leaving your post, defecting to the enemy.

201
00:13:38.317 --> 00:13:40.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you calling Odo your enemy?
<i>-Absolutely not.</i>

202
00:13:40.986 --> 00:13:44.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was referring to the Federation,
as you're well aware.

203
00:13:44.281 --> 00:13:47.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Enough bickering. Order him to trigger
his implant.

204
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:49.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was getting to that.

205
00:13:50.329 --> 00:13:51.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What implant?

206
00:13:51.747 --> 00:13:53.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like all Vorta,

207
00:13:53.207 --> 00:13:55.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a termination implant
in my brain stem.

208
00:13:55.751 --> 00:13:59.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prove your loyalty
to the Founders activate it.

209
00:13:59.213 --> 00:14:02.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The only Founder I'm loyal to is Odo,
and he wants me alive.

210
00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:05.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I told you it was a waste of time</i>
<i>trying to reason with him.</i>

211
00:14:06.512 --> 00:14:09.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're a dead man</i>
<i>whether you activate the implant or not.</i>

212
00:14:09.557 --> 00:14:12.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That ship will never make it back </i>
<i>to Deep Space 9.</i>

213
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:14.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Founder, there's really no need</i>

214
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>for you to be involved</i>
<i>in this petty dispute.</i>

215
00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:20.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If you'll just hold your position</i>
<i>until one of our ships can reach you.</i>

216
00:14:20.818 --> 00:14:23.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have no intention of releasing
my prisoner to you.

217
00:14:24.238 --> 00:14:25.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WEYOUN 7: <i>If you don't,</i>

218
00:14:25.197 --> 00:14:27.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can't be responsible </i>
<i>for the consequences.</i>

219
00:14:27.199 --> 00:14:30.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's an empty threat.
He wouldn't dare harm a Founder.

220
00:14:30.661 --> 00:14:33.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe he won't, but I will.

221
00:14:34.373 --> 00:14:37.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Think it over, shape-shifter.</i>
<i>One of our attack ships is on the way.</i>

222
00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:49.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forgive me, Odo.

223
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:52.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should have told you
the truth about myself.

224
00:14:52.308 --> 00:14:54.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's not too late to start.

225
00:14:56.228 --> 00:14:57.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did you defect?

226
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's quite simple really.

227
00:15:01.358 --> 00:15:06.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From the moment I was activated,
I felt this war was wrong.

228
00:15:07.114 --> 00:15:10.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please don't misunderstand me.
I still worship the Founders,

229
00:15:10.743 --> 00:15:12.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I believe their obsession

230
00:15:12.620 --> 00:15:16.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with conquering the Alpha
Quadrant is misguided.

231
00:15:16.206 --> 00:15:19.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's time they learned to live in peace
with the solids.

232
00:15:20.419 --> 00:15:23.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know it's not my place
to question the Founders.

233
00:15:26.342 --> 00:15:28.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe Weyoun 7 is right.

234
00:15:30.054 --> 00:15:31.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am defective.

235
00:15:33.641 --> 00:15:34.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On the contrary.

236
00:15:35.017 --> 00:15:36.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What you're saying, about the war,

237
00:15:36.727 --> 00:15:38.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
about the Founders...

238
00:15:39.688 --> 00:15:41.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Makes perfect sense.

239
00:15:44.109 --> 00:15:45.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to thank you, Odo

240
00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:48.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for the way you stood up for me,
protected me.

241
00:15:48.697 --> 00:15:50.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, don't let it go to your head.

242
00:15:50.824 --> 00:15:52.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd do the same for any prisoner.

243
00:15:53.118 --> 00:15:54.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course, you would.

244
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:56.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're a God.

245
00:16:09.843 --> 00:16:15.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To think a Weyoun
could be capable of such treachery.

246
00:16:16.392 --> 00:16:18.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I knew there was something wrong with him
from the moment we met.

247
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:21.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He lacked your appetite for cruelty.

248
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:25.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a disgrace to me and all Vorta.

249
00:16:26.318 --> 00:16:32.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Though... I suppose he can't be held
completely responsible for his behavior.

250
00:16:33.117 --> 00:16:36.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Vorta cloning process
is a very delicate one.

251
00:16:36.954 --> 00:16:41.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every once in a while, a clone is found
to be defective.

252
00:16:41.959 --> 00:16:45.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's never happened to a Weyoun before
but, it does happen.

253
00:16:46.964 --> 00:16:50.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And speaking of treachery...

254
00:16:51.468 --> 00:16:55.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there is still the little matter
of the death of Weyoun 5.

255
00:16:55.848 --> 00:16:57.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You really believe I had something
to do with that?

256
00:16:57.599 --> 00:16:59.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You were supposed
to be on that transporter pad with him.

257
00:17:00.060 --> 00:17:01.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was called away, urgent meeting
with Central Command.

258
00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:03.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How convenient.

259
00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:05.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I always was lucky.
-Hmm.

260
00:17:06.525 --> 00:17:08.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you sure I can't interest you
in a glass of <i>kanar?</i>

261
00:17:10.154 --> 00:17:14.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid our problems won't be washed
away quite that easily.

262
00:17:14.575 --> 00:17:16.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know
what you're so concerned about.

263
00:17:16.243 --> 00:17:18.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo couldn't possibly hope to outrun
a Jem'Hadar attack ship.

264
00:17:18.912 --> 00:17:22.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if he refuses
to hand over his prisoner?

265
00:17:22.875 --> 00:17:23.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then he'll die.

266
00:17:24.251 --> 00:17:28.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He will not.
We can't kill a Founder. I forbid it.

267
00:17:29.298 --> 00:17:33.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unless we stop them, Odo is going to take
your predecessor back to the Federation

268
00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:35.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where he will undoubtedly
reveal all he knows,

269
00:17:35.929 --> 00:17:38.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all you know,
about our strategic operations.

270
00:17:38.640 --> 00:17:42.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You know what that means, don't you?
-It means we could lose the war.

271
00:17:43.145 --> 00:17:46.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right.
And I will not allow that to happen.

272
00:17:47.524 --> 00:17:50.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cardassia has risked too much,
suffered too much.

273
00:17:50.152 --> 00:17:52.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I will not stand by
and let all of our plans,

274
00:17:52.404 --> 00:17:55.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all of our dreams
for the future end in defeat

275
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:57.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just to spare the life
of one shape-shifter.

276
00:17:57.701 --> 00:18:00.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't believe the Jem'Hadar
are going to fire on Odo,

277
00:18:00.579 --> 00:18:01.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
even if they're ordered to.

278
00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:06.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They don't need to know he's on board.

279
00:18:07.544 --> 00:18:10.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You simply order them
to destroy the runabout.

280
00:18:13.717 --> 00:18:15.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose it could work.

281
00:18:16.053 --> 00:18:20.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if the Founders ever found out that we
were responsible for Odo's death...

282
00:18:20.808 --> 00:18:22.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's going to tell them?

283
00:18:27.773 --> 00:18:32.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo doesn't even consider himself
a Founder.

284
00:18:33.237 --> 00:18:34.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we agree.

285
00:18:35.781 --> 00:18:37.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The runabout must be destroyed.

286
00:18:43.497 --> 00:18:44.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excellent.

287
00:18:46.166 --> 00:18:49.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, I really think you
should try a little <i>kanar.</i>

288
00:19:03.267 --> 00:19:05.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

289
00:19:11.692 --> 00:19:15.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Morning, Lieutenant.
-I'd make myself scarce if I were you.

290
00:19:15.112 --> 00:19:16.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why?
-KIRA: Chief.

291
00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:18.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In here now.

292
00:19:19.575 --> 00:19:20.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tried to warn you.

293
00:19:28.167 --> 00:19:30.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you mind explaining this?

294
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where's the Captain's desk?
-Oh, you don't know?

295
00:19:33.964 --> 00:19:35.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is your authorization code, isn't it?

296
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Nog.
-What about him?

297
00:19:41.013 --> 00:19:43.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He must have traded the Captain's desk

298
00:19:43.473 --> 00:19:45.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-for the graviton stabilizer.
-Excuse me?

299
00:19:45.893 --> 00:19:47.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Colonel.
I will get the desk back.

300
00:19:47.936 --> 00:19:49.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you're damn right, you will.

301
00:19:49.688 --> 00:19:51.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Captain is returning
from Bajor in two days,

302
00:19:52.357 --> 00:19:57.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and when he does, I want his desk
sitting right here, where it belongs.

303
00:19:57.571 --> 00:20:00.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Chief. I didn't give away
the Captain's desk.

304
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:02.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I just loaned it to someone.
-Who?

305
00:20:02.826 --> 00:20:05.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Al Lorenzo.
-Who's Al Lorenzo?

306
00:20:05.829 --> 00:20:08.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Chief of Operations on Decos Prime.

307
00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:10.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does he want with the Captain's desk?

308
00:20:10.125 --> 00:20:12.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He wants to take a picture of it.

309
00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:13.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

310
00:20:13.921 --> 00:20:16.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He likes to collect holophotos of himself

311
00:20:16.381 --> 00:20:19.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
sitting behind the desks
of famous Starfleet Captains.

312
00:20:19.718 --> 00:20:21.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Usually, he just sneaks
into their offices,

313
00:20:21.762 --> 00:20:24.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but with the war on, it's been hard
for him to get away.

314
00:20:24.473 --> 00:20:25.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that makes sense.

315
00:20:26.183 --> 00:20:30.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's got quite a collection.
Captain DeSoto's desk, Captain Picard's--

316
00:20:30.187 --> 00:20:35.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, fine. So... once he has his picture,

317
00:20:35.817 --> 00:20:38.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he's going to send us
the graviton stabilizer.

318
00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:41.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. He's giving us an induction modulator.

319
00:20:41.323 --> 00:20:43.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we don't need an induction modulator.

320
00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:44.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But the USS <i>Musashi </i>does.

321
00:20:46.078 --> 00:20:46.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah...

322
00:20:47.204 --> 00:20:50.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so the <i>Musashi's </i>going
to send us the stabilizer.

323
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:52.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. They're giving us a phaser emitter.

324
00:20:52.209 --> 00:20:54.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we don't need a phaser emitter.

325
00:20:54.461 --> 00:20:59.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know, but the USS <i>Sentinel </i>does,
and they have the extra stabilizer.

326
00:20:59.174 --> 00:21:01.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And they're willing to give
it up for a phaser emitter?

327
00:21:01.802 --> 00:21:03.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's the rumor.
-Rumor?

328
00:21:04.304 --> 00:21:06.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've made all these deals
based on a rumor?

329
00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:08.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
From a very reliable source.

330
00:21:09.142 --> 00:21:10.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, what if it turns out not to be true?

331
00:21:10.477 --> 00:21:12.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have to have faith, Chief.

332
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:16.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-In a rumor?
-No. In the Great Material Continuum.

333
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:20.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who are they?

334
00:21:20.779 --> 00:21:24.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not a "they." It's the force
that binds the universe together.

335
00:21:25.575 --> 00:21:28.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must have missed that class
in engineering school.

336
00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:29.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
NOG: On Ferenginar, we learn about
the Continuum

337
00:21:30.038 --> 00:21:32.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
while we still have our first set of ears.

338
00:21:32.499 --> 00:21:35.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no time for Ferengi fairy tales.

339
00:21:35.210 --> 00:21:37.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Continuum is real.

340
00:21:39.881 --> 00:21:43.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see, there are millions
upon millions of worlds

341
00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:47.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the universe, each one filled
with too much of one thing

342
00:21:47.556 --> 00:21:49.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and not enough of another.

343
00:21:49.099 --> 00:21:51.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Great Continuum
flows through them all

344
00:21:52.019 --> 00:21:55.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
like a mighty river,
from have to want and back again.

345
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:58.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And, if we navigate the Continuum

346
00:21:58.859 --> 00:22:00.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with skill and grace,

347
00:22:00.819 --> 00:22:04.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
our ship will be filled
with everything our hearts desire.

348
00:22:05.032 --> 00:22:06.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, right now,
I'd settle for a stabilizer

349
00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:08.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the Captain's desk.

350
00:22:10.662 --> 00:22:12.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The river will provide.

351
00:22:12.247 --> 00:22:14.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( scoffs ) If it doesn't sink us first.

352
00:22:20.255 --> 00:22:23.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( mumbling )

353
00:22:24.801 --> 00:22:25.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo?

354
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:30.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

355
00:22:31.099 --> 00:22:33.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

356
00:22:33.894 --> 00:22:35.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's wrong?

357
00:22:36.688 --> 00:22:40.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I was... dreaming.

358
00:22:41.318 --> 00:22:43.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sounded more like a nightmare.

359
00:22:45.906 --> 00:22:51.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was on Earth...
Starfleet Headquarters.

360
00:22:51.119 --> 00:22:57.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was supposed to report for my debriefing
but I couldn't find the right office.

361
00:22:58.460 --> 00:23:02.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then I started calling your name,
but you didn't answer.

362
00:23:03.381 --> 00:23:07.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then suddenly...
I was being chased by some Jem'Hadar...

363
00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:11.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or were they Klingons?

364
00:23:11.848 --> 00:23:13.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

365
00:23:18.939 --> 00:23:20.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Silly, isn't it?

366
00:23:21.983 --> 00:23:23.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not at all.

367
00:23:24.361 --> 00:23:27.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It isn't easy to turn your back
on your own people.

368
00:23:28.865 --> 00:23:30.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Believe me, I know.

369
00:23:33.537 --> 00:23:36.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Odo, do you think Starfleet
would allow you

370
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:38.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to conduct my debriefing?

371
00:23:43.171 --> 00:23:44.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Possibly.

372
00:23:46.633 --> 00:23:49.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It would make it much easier.

373
00:23:49.261 --> 00:23:50.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

374
00:23:50.387 --> 00:23:51.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( alarm blares )

375
00:23:51.555 --> 00:23:53.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it?
-Trouble.

376
00:24:10.991 --> 00:24:12.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe they're firing on us.

377
00:24:14.661 --> 00:24:15.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trust me, they are.

378
00:24:15.704 --> 00:24:18.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But the Jem'Hadar would never obey
an order to harm a Founder.

379
00:24:18.665 --> 00:24:21.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe they finally got it through
their head that I'm not a Founder.

380
00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:24.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or they don't know who they're firing at.

381
00:24:25.046 --> 00:24:26.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got to let them know
you're on board.

382
00:24:26.798 --> 00:24:29.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're jamming all the frequencies.
I can't get through.

383
00:24:29.885 --> 00:24:32.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've been ordered
not to communicate with us.

384
00:24:32.762 --> 00:24:36.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damar said he was determined
not to let us get back to the station.

385
00:24:40.353 --> 00:24:42.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See if you can get above them.

386
00:24:43.023 --> 00:24:43.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

387
00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:45.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll explain later. Just do it.

388
00:24:52.699 --> 00:24:53.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What now?

389
00:24:54.326 --> 00:24:56.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Lock phasers on their dorsal
field junction.

390
00:24:56.536 --> 00:24:58.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Their shields are weakest there.

391
00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:15.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, congratulations.

392
00:25:16.514 --> 00:25:18.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've just saved our lives.

393
00:25:19.226 --> 00:25:22.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And murdered loyal servants
of the Dominion.

394
00:25:23.021 --> 00:25:25.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
May the Founders forgive me.

395
00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:30.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Has it ever occurred to you

396
00:25:30.362 --> 00:25:33.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the reason you believe
the Founders are Gods

397
00:25:33.198 --> 00:25:35.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is because that's what they want
you to believe?

398
00:25:35.992 --> 00:25:38.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That they built it into your genetic code?

399
00:25:38.536 --> 00:25:41.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course they did.
That's what Gods do.

400
00:25:41.957 --> 00:25:46.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After all, why be a God if there's no one
to worship you.

401
00:25:56.596 --> 00:25:58.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom, where's Nog?

402
00:25:58.515 --> 00:26:02.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know, Chief. Nog left the station
a couple of hours ago in a runabout.

403
00:26:02.560 --> 00:26:04.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Who gave him permission
to use a runabout?

404
00:26:04.437 --> 00:26:05.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You did.

405
00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:08.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh! I never should have given
him my authorization code.

406
00:26:10.277 --> 00:26:11.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did he say when he'd be back?

407
00:26:11.695 --> 00:26:12.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not to me.

408
00:26:12.988 --> 00:26:14.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could he do this to me?

409
00:26:15.657 --> 00:26:18.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How could he leave me adrift
mid-river without a paddle?

410
00:26:18.910 --> 00:26:20.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What river would that be?

411
00:26:20.787 --> 00:26:23.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, the Great Material Continuum.

412
00:26:23.623 --> 00:26:26.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, that river.
It can be very treacherous.

413
00:26:27.335 --> 00:26:29.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me about it.

414
00:26:29.296 --> 00:26:33.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suppose the good news is, with Nog gone,
nothing else can go missing.

415
00:26:35.135 --> 00:26:38.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are my cases of bloodwine?

416
00:26:38.305 --> 00:26:39.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

417
00:26:40.307 --> 00:26:43.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I do not know, General,
but I promise you I will find out.

418
00:26:43.935 --> 00:26:46.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( snarling growl )

419
00:26:46.104 --> 00:26:47.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( kicks crate )

420
00:26:51.776 --> 00:26:53.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAMAR: I don't understand it.

421
00:26:53.236 --> 00:26:55.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How could a runabout destroy
a Jem'Hadar fighter?

422
00:26:55.655 --> 00:26:58.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Isn't it obvious?
My predecessor must have helped Odo

423
00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:00.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
get past the ship's defenses.

424
00:27:00.368 --> 00:27:02.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Then how do we stop them?
-How else? Send more ships.

425
00:27:02.704 --> 00:27:06.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Send a whole battalion if necessary
from our base at Olmerak.

426
00:27:06.166 --> 00:27:07.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Consider it done.

427
00:27:08.668 --> 00:27:10.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember to tell them to fire on sight.

428
00:27:11.421 --> 00:27:12.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
FEMALE SHAPE-SHIFTER: Fire at whom?

429
00:27:14.632 --> 00:27:17.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Founder, how may I serve you?

430
00:27:18.386 --> 00:27:20.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By answering my question.

431
00:27:21.056 --> 00:27:25.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We spotted a Federation runabout spying
on our base in the Olmerak system.

432
00:27:25.810 --> 00:27:28.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Surely one ship
shouldn't be much of a threat.

433
00:27:28.521 --> 00:27:31.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll have it destroyed within the hour.

434
00:27:31.691 --> 00:27:33.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling all right?

435
00:27:34.194 --> 00:27:35.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why do you ask?

436
00:27:36.363 --> 00:27:37.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your face.

437
00:27:43.203 --> 00:27:44.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm fine.

438
00:27:45.497 --> 00:27:47.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But from now on,
I want the temperature in these rooms

439
00:27:47.665 --> 00:27:49.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
lowered by 15 degrees.

440
00:27:49.751 --> 00:27:52.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I do not share
the Cardassians' love of heat.

441
00:27:53.046 --> 00:27:55.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nor do I. Lower the temperature.

442
00:27:55.924 --> 00:27:57.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As you wish.

443
00:27:58.134 --> 00:28:00.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything else I can do for you?

444
00:28:00.261 --> 00:28:02.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you located Weyoun 6?

445
00:28:02.806 --> 00:28:05.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's only a matter of time.
-So you keep saying.

446
00:28:06.393 --> 00:28:09.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assure you, Founder,
he will be dealt with.

447
00:28:16.986 --> 00:28:20.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you notice her face?
How parched it looked?

448
00:28:20.990 --> 00:28:23.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You heard her. These rooms are too hot.

449
00:28:23.326 --> 00:28:26.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wonder.
I'm telling you she's not well.

450
00:28:26.996 --> 00:28:29.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's not the Founder
you should be worried about.

451
00:28:29.916 --> 00:28:33.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Contact Olmerak and order those ships
to intercept the runabout.

452
00:28:44.806 --> 00:28:47.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mmm... mmm-mmm.

453
00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:53.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( clatters )

454
00:28:55.525 --> 00:28:56.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

455
00:28:57.569 --> 00:28:58.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was filling.

456
00:28:59.738 --> 00:29:00.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would hope so.

457
00:29:00.864 --> 00:29:03.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've sampled
the replicator's entire menu.

458
00:29:03.908 --> 00:29:07.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I enjoyed the different... textures.

459
00:29:08.830 --> 00:29:10.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean tastes, don't you?

460
00:29:11.124 --> 00:29:14.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not at all. The Vorta's sense of taste
is quite limited.

461
00:29:14.169 --> 00:29:16.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
About the only foods we really enjoy

462
00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:18.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are <i>kava </i>nuts and rippleberries.

463
00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:21.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. I take it

464
00:29:21.134 --> 00:29:24.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this is also the result
of your genetic programming?

465
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:28.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the Founder's way of making sure
we remember our past.

466
00:29:29.517 --> 00:29:32.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You must know the story
of how the Founders created the Vorta?

467
00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:35.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) No.

468
00:29:36.566 --> 00:29:40.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have the feeling
you're going to tell me all about it.

469
00:29:43.323 --> 00:29:48.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Vorta used to be quite different
from what we are today.

470
00:29:48.244 --> 00:29:53.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We were forest dwellers, small, timid,
ape-like creatures,

471
00:29:53.249 --> 00:29:54.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
living in hollowed-out trees.

472
00:29:54.876 --> 00:29:59.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Eating nuts and berries.
And living in fear of the many predators

473
00:29:59.714 --> 00:30:01.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that would hunt us for food.

474
00:30:01.841 --> 00:30:05.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One day, a wounded changeling
came stumbling through the forest,

475
00:30:05.762 --> 00:30:07.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
fleeing from a mob of angry solids.

476
00:30:07.931 --> 00:30:11.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why were they chasing him?
-What does it matter?

477
00:30:11.976 --> 00:30:14.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Solids have always feared
and mistrusted shape-shifters.

478
00:30:14.562 --> 00:30:15.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know that.

479
00:30:16.523 --> 00:30:21.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, a family of Vorta
hid the changeling from his pursuers,

480
00:30:22.028 --> 00:30:24.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and in exchange for saving his life,

481
00:30:24.572 --> 00:30:28.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the changeling promised
the Vorta that one day

482
00:30:28.451 --> 00:30:32.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we would be transformed
into powerful beings,

483
00:30:33.206 --> 00:30:38.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that we would become an important part
of a great new empire

484
00:30:38.378 --> 00:30:43.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-that would stretch across the galaxy.
-And the changeling kept his word?

485
00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:46.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right. Imagine, Odo,

486
00:30:47.053 --> 00:30:51.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my people were once little more than apes,
and look at us now.

487
00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:54.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look at what you've done for us.

488
00:30:57.647 --> 00:31:00.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the story were true,
it would at least prove

489
00:31:00.567 --> 00:31:05.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that my people are capable
of generosity and kindness.

490
00:31:08.658 --> 00:31:11.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You care about your people
very much, don't you, Odo,

491
00:31:11.953 --> 00:31:13.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in spite of all that's happened
between you?

492
00:31:16.249 --> 00:31:19.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe I do,
but that doesn't change the fact

493
00:31:19.752 --> 00:31:22.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that they're responsible for a war
that's killed millions.

494
00:31:24.257 --> 00:31:28.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo, there's something you need to know.

495
00:31:30.179 --> 00:31:33.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A sickness has spread
throughout the Great Link.

496
00:31:34.350 --> 00:31:35.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Founders...

497
00:31:37.645 --> 00:31:38.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are dying.

498
00:31:51.367 --> 00:31:54.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was summoned to a meeting
by the female changeling.

499
00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:56.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She wanted to discuss
troop deployments with me,

500
00:31:56.664 --> 00:31:59.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and suddenly, her hands began to...

501
00:32:00.043 --> 00:32:01.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shrivel.

502
00:32:02.045 --> 00:32:04.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It lasted only a second or two,

503
00:32:04.714 --> 00:32:07.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but over the last few weeks
it's happened a number of times.

504
00:32:08.051 --> 00:32:10.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's like she's... withering.

505
00:32:13.222 --> 00:32:17.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you're sure
the other changelings are also infected?

506
00:32:18.144 --> 00:32:21.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She said the entire Link
is suffering from the disease.

507
00:32:26.361 --> 00:32:27.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everyone but me.

508
00:32:28.988 --> 00:32:32.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they're unable to find a cure,
you'll be the last of your kind.

509
00:32:37.830 --> 00:32:42.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why didn't you tell me this earlier?
Because I knew how much it would hurt you.

510
00:32:42.710 --> 00:32:48.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sorry to bring you such sad news,
but at least you're not infected.

511
00:32:49.717 --> 00:32:52.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion will survive.

512
00:32:54.097 --> 00:32:55.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

513
00:32:55.723 --> 00:32:59.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Think about it, Odo.
You have an opportunity

514
00:33:00.311 --> 00:33:03.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to rectify the mistakes
your people have made.

515
00:33:03.523 --> 00:33:08.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To build a new Dominion
based on cooperation, not conquest,

516
00:33:08.736 --> 00:33:14.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on peace, not war,
a new order under your leadership.

517
00:33:15.994 --> 00:33:19.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what's your role going
to be in this "new order"?

518
00:33:20.873 --> 00:33:23.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever you want it to be.

519
00:33:24.210 --> 00:33:26.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish only to serve you.

520
00:33:29.382 --> 00:33:31.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( beeping )
( alarm blaring )

521
00:33:31.551 --> 00:33:33.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

522
00:33:33.428 --> 00:33:35.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you can start
by telling me how one runabout

523
00:33:35.888 --> 00:33:38.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is going to survive an assault
by four Jem'Hadar ships.

524
00:33:39.058 --> 00:33:41.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sure you'll think of something.

525
00:33:49.694 --> 00:33:51.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a Kuiper belt not far from here.

526
00:33:51.779 --> 00:33:55.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We might be able to hide
among the comet fragments.

527
00:33:55.283 --> 00:33:58.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we don't have much time.
They're closing fast.

528
00:34:17.180 --> 00:34:20.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
These comet fragments
are nothing but huge chunks of ice.

529
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:22.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Jem'Hadar will have
no trouble finding us.

530
00:34:23.853 --> 00:34:25.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if we become the ice.

531
00:34:47.835 --> 00:34:50.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( equipment powering down )

532
00:34:51.297 --> 00:34:53.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, with the power off

533
00:34:53.132 --> 00:34:55.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and the runabout in thermal
contact with the ice,

534
00:34:55.843 --> 00:34:58.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we won't generate enough
of an energy signature

535
00:34:58.387 --> 00:35:00.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for their sensors to read.

536
00:35:00.139 --> 00:35:02.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"We become the ice."

537
00:35:03.851 --> 00:35:06.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Only a God could think of such a thing.

538
00:35:06.687 --> 00:35:08.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, let's just hope the Jem'Hadar
give up their search

539
00:35:08.981 --> 00:35:10.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before we freeze to death.

540
00:35:10.650 --> 00:35:12.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My faith will keep me warm.

541
00:35:12.777 --> 00:35:15.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. Perhaps, but in an hour,

542
00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:19.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you may want to trade
in that faith for a thermal blanket.

543
00:35:24.122 --> 00:35:25.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

544
00:35:26.124 --> 00:35:26.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's white.

545
00:35:27.667 --> 00:35:29.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know it's white.

546
00:35:29.085 --> 00:35:30.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to paint it.

547
00:35:31.462 --> 00:35:32.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the wrong shape.

548
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:36.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the wrong height, the wrong width.

549
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:38.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Other than that, it's perfect.

550
00:35:38.928 --> 00:35:41.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Captain'll never suspect
you switched desks on him.

551
00:35:41.597 --> 00:35:45.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Julian, I need help, not sarcasm.

552
00:35:45.726 --> 00:35:47.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid Nog's the only one
who can help you now.

553
00:35:47.770 --> 00:35:50.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If he gets back to the station
before the Captain does.

554
00:35:51.149 --> 00:35:54.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe he's not coming back.
Maybe he's decided to make a run for it.

555
00:35:57.405 --> 00:35:58.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That isn't the Captain's desk.

556
00:35:58.823 --> 00:35:59.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's going to paint it.

557
00:36:00.533 --> 00:36:02.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get it out of here!

558
00:36:02.910 --> 00:36:03.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I help you, General?

559
00:36:04.036 --> 00:36:06.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No... but he can!

560
00:36:09.375 --> 00:36:10.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: Bloodwine?

561
00:36:10.877 --> 00:36:16.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sixteen cases... sent to me by my wife.
Now, where are they?

562
00:36:17.008 --> 00:36:20.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, how... how should I know?
-You authorized their removal.

563
00:36:21.095 --> 00:36:24.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That is your authorization code,
is it not?

564
00:36:24.724 --> 00:36:25.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog.

565
00:36:26.058 --> 00:36:26.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief...

566
00:36:28.769 --> 00:36:32.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want that bloodwine
back here by tomorrow.

567
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:35.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Understood?

568
00:36:40.072 --> 00:36:43.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( shivering )

569
00:36:44.118 --> 00:36:44.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo...

570
00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:49.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when you said
you were cutting power to all systems,

571
00:36:49.624 --> 00:36:51.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
did that include life-support?

572
00:36:52.543 --> 00:36:53.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid so.

573
00:36:54.295 --> 00:36:56.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. That explains it.

574
00:36:56.756 --> 00:36:57.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Explains what?

575
00:36:57.798 --> 00:37:00.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why I'm having trouble breathing.

576
00:37:02.929 --> 00:37:06.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should have enough oxygen left
for another three hours.

577
00:37:07.058 --> 00:37:10.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, by then,
we will have probably frozen to death.

578
00:37:10.978 --> 00:37:12.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you can't die.

579
00:37:13.105 --> 00:37:16.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have to survive
to rebuild the Dominion.

580
00:37:18.069 --> 00:37:20.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( explosion )

581
00:37:20.363 --> 00:37:21.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They found us.

582
00:37:32.208 --> 00:37:34.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What do we do now?
-We can't stay here.

583
00:37:34.835 --> 00:37:37.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're not going to try
to outrun those ships, are you?

584
00:37:37.672 --> 00:37:39.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What choice do we have?

585
00:38:06.158 --> 00:38:08.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're on fire.
-There's an extinguisher behind you.

586
00:38:11.831 --> 00:38:13.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you waiting for?

587
00:38:15.876 --> 00:38:18.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I live only to serve you.

588
00:38:33.185 --> 00:38:35.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( com console beeping )

589
00:38:35.855 --> 00:38:38.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are you doing? Why have you activated
the com system?

590
00:38:41.277 --> 00:38:43.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right. Call off those ships.

591
00:38:43.404 --> 00:38:44.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why should I? </i>

592
00:38:44.655 --> 00:38:47.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because you don't need
them anymore.

593
00:38:50.703 --> 00:38:53.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm glad to see </i>
<i>you've come to your senses.</i>

594
00:38:55.041 --> 00:38:56.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What have you done?

595
00:38:56.542 --> 00:38:59.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've saved your life,
and the Dominion's as well.

596
00:38:59.920 --> 00:39:02.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>He's activated his termination implant</i>

597
00:39:02.214 --> 00:39:04.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and proven himself </i>
<i>to be a worthy Vorta at last.</i>

598
00:39:05.343 --> 00:39:07.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I obey the Founders in all things.

599
00:39:10.806 --> 00:39:12.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now call off those ships!

600
00:39:13.059 --> 00:39:16.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't know what he told Odo.
He may have revealed important tactical...

601
00:39:16.354 --> 00:39:18.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a risk we'll just have to take.

602
00:39:18.564 --> 00:39:19.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

603
00:39:20.066 --> 00:39:22.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've ordered the Jem'Hadar
to break off the attack.

604
00:39:23.402 --> 00:39:26.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I see your runabout has suffered
some battle damage.

605
00:39:26.155 --> 00:39:27.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Will you require any further assistance?

606
00:39:28.074 --> 00:39:29.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think you've done enough!

607
00:39:30.034 --> 00:39:35.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I sincerely regret any... inconvenience</i>
<i>we may have caused you, Odo.</i>

608
00:39:35.956 --> 00:39:40.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Please have a safe and pleasant journey</i>
<i>back to Deep Space 9.</i>

609
00:39:42.630 --> 00:39:46.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They say voluntary termination
is quick and painless.

610
00:39:46.675 --> 00:39:48.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid it's not true.

611
00:39:48.177 --> 00:39:49.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll get you a pain suppresser.

612
00:39:49.595 --> 00:39:53.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That won't be necessary,
but there is one thing you can do for me.

613
00:39:53.516 --> 00:39:54.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

614
00:39:54.892 --> 00:39:56.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give me your blessing.

615
00:39:58.521 --> 00:39:59.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I can't.

616
00:39:59.522 --> 00:40:00.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, Odo.

617
00:40:01.482 --> 00:40:04.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell me I haven't failed,
that I've served you well.

618
00:40:04.568 --> 00:40:07.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have,
and for that you have my gratitude...

619
00:40:10.658 --> 00:40:13.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and... my blessing.

620
00:40:41.856 --> 00:40:43.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, the Captain's back.

621
00:40:43.941 --> 00:40:45.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know. He sent for me.

622
00:40:45.693 --> 00:40:46.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

623
00:40:47.778 --> 00:40:48.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

624
00:40:52.950 --> 00:40:54.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, Chief.

625
00:40:55.035 --> 00:40:56.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain, your desk...

626
00:40:56.662 --> 00:40:58.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it looks nice, doesn't it?

627
00:40:58.706 --> 00:41:01.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I came in this morning and found
Ensign Nog polishing it.

628
00:41:01.542 --> 00:41:03.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was looking a little dull.

629
00:41:03.711 --> 00:41:07.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, here is the maintenance request
from the <i>Gettysburg.</i>

630
00:41:07.089 --> 00:41:08.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should be docking here later today.

631
00:41:09.508 --> 00:41:10.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That'll be all.

632
00:41:11.677 --> 00:41:12.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

633
00:41:13.387 --> 00:41:15.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, about the stabilizer...

634
00:41:15.264 --> 00:41:17.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain, I-I can explain.
-SISKO: Don't bother.

635
00:41:17.892 --> 00:41:21.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ensign Nog tells me you were able
to get a hold of one this morning.

636
00:41:22.313 --> 00:41:23.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was?

637
00:41:23.814 --> 00:41:24.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, I was.

638
00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:26.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long before you can have it on line?

639
00:41:27.860 --> 00:41:29.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Um... eight hours.

640
00:41:29.987 --> 00:41:33.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I plan to take the <i>Defiant</i>
out on patrol in two.

641
00:41:33.157 --> 00:41:34.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Two it is, sir.

642
00:41:37.203 --> 00:41:39.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how you did it, Nog.

643
00:41:39.121 --> 00:41:42.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never lost faith
in the Great Material Continuum.

644
00:41:42.416 --> 00:41:44.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, like you say, the River will provide.

645
00:41:44.210 --> 00:41:45.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief!

646
00:41:45.794 --> 00:41:47.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The waters just got choppy again.

647
00:41:49.048 --> 00:41:50.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want you to have this.

648
00:41:50.549 --> 00:41:52.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Consider it an apology.

649
00:41:52.426 --> 00:41:53.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... you found the bloodwine?

650
00:41:54.094 --> 00:41:56.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not exactly. Ensign Nog
returned from his trip

651
00:41:56.889 --> 00:42:01.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with 16 cases of 2309,
a very good year.

652
00:42:01.894 --> 00:42:05.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
An even better vintage
than the one my wife sent me.

653
00:42:05.189 --> 00:42:06.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

654
00:42:07.024 --> 00:42:09.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I'm, uh...
I'm glad you approve.

655
00:42:09.401 --> 00:42:10.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And remember,

656
00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:12.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
any time you're shopping
for wines or spirits,

657
00:42:12.947 --> 00:42:14.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my Cousin Gant is the man to see.

658
00:42:14.740 --> 00:42:16.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will keep that in mind.

659
00:42:18.869 --> 00:42:20.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your Cousin Gant?

660
00:42:20.246 --> 00:42:22.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just another sailor on the Great River.
-Ah...

661
00:42:22.414 --> 00:42:26.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By the way, Gant mentioned
he's got ten cases of Saurian brandy.

662
00:42:26.085 --> 00:42:27.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the Captain's favorite, you know.

663
00:42:27.962 --> 00:42:29.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Level 5.

664
00:42:29.838 --> 00:42:31.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What does he want for them?

665
00:42:34.176 --> 00:42:37.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think I'll ever forget
the look on his face when he died.

666
00:42:37.972 --> 00:42:41.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He seemed so... content.

667
00:42:42.393 --> 00:42:43.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The last thing he saw

668
00:42:43.602 --> 00:42:48.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was one of his Gods smiling at him.
If you ask me, he was a lucky man.

669
00:42:50.067 --> 00:42:51.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys, please.

670
00:42:51.485 --> 00:42:53.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, listen to me.

671
00:42:54.321 --> 00:42:55.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know to Starfleet

672
00:42:56.073 --> 00:42:59.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Prophets are nothing
more than wormhole aliens,

673
00:42:59.994 --> 00:43:02.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but to me, they're Gods.

674
00:43:03.622 --> 00:43:06.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
KIRA: I can't prove it.
Then, again, I don't have to,

675
00:43:06.750 --> 00:43:08.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
because my faith in them is enough,

676
00:43:09.795 --> 00:43:14.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just as Weyoun's faith in you...
was enough for him.

677
00:43:17.595 --> 00:43:19.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, now it appears that the Vorta

678
00:43:19.680 --> 00:43:22.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
may have to learn
to get along without their Gods.

679
00:43:23.017 --> 00:43:24.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

680
00:43:27.104 --> 00:43:28.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're worried about your people.

681
00:43:32.568 --> 00:43:36.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The changelings are dying,
and I can't help them.

682
00:43:37.323 --> 00:43:41.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They're the enemy.
-A very dangerous enemy.

683
00:43:41.994 --> 00:43:43.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now more than ever,

684
00:43:43.829 --> 00:43:45.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
because they're all so desperate.

685
00:43:46.165 --> 00:43:48.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) This isn't easy for you,

686
00:43:48.834 --> 00:43:51.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you have to remember
they started this war.

687
00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:52.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You didn't.

688
00:43:52.838 --> 00:43:54.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's true...

689
00:43:55.883 --> 00:43:57.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I know now

690
00:43:57.968 --> 00:44:01.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
whichever side wins,
one thing is certain...

691
00:44:03.390 --> 00:44:05.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to lose.

